              },
              "free_text": [
                "Experiment was conducted using TUNL's",
                "High-Intensity Gamma-Ray Source (HIgS) at the Duke",
                "Free-Electron-Laser Laboratory"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 241Am targets were produced and chemically",
                "purified at Los Alamos National Laboratory as a",
                "dried nitrate powder. Six electroplated targets about",
                "0.8 mg/cm2 thick and 1 cm in diameter were used. Each",
                "Americium target was sandwiched between an upstream",
                "and downstream set of Au and Ni monitoring foils 1 cm",
                "in  diameter and 25 mu-m in thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two independent 60% HPGe detectors were used",
                "to count off line each monitor foil pack and the",
                "americium target. The absolute efficiency of the",
                "HPGe detectors at 1.33 MeV was 0.0150 +- 0.0003."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
